params.aSender: The initial msg.sender for the swap call

cancelOwnershipHandover().details: Cancels the two-step ownership handover to the caller, if any.

claimFees(address,address).details: User balances are never stored in Angstrom so this is         non-custodial. Additionally, it could allow for recovery in the         case of funds that got stuck in this contract.

params.aCurrency: The Currency (ERC20 or ETH) to transfer.

completeOwnershipHandover(address).details: Allows the owner to complete the two-step ownership handover to `pendingOwner`. Reverts if there is no existing ownership handover requested by `pendingOwner`.

invalidateUnorderedNonces(uint256,uint25.details: The wordPos is maxed at type(uint248).max

params.mask: A bitmap masked against msg.sender's current bitmap at the word position
params.wordPos: A number to index the nonceBitmap at

lockAcquired(bytes).details: We do not check that the caller is the poolManager, as all the         calls we make in this function will revert if we are not the         active locker.

owner().details: Returns the owner of the contract.

ownershipHandoverExpiresAt(address).details: Returns the expiry timestamp for the two-step ownership handover to `pendingOwner`.

process((((uint256,uint8,address,address.details: The Angstrom bundle validates user constraints and then follows         the instructions laid out by the guard network.

params.aBundle: The bundle to process for this round.

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the owner to renounce their ownership.

requestOwnershipHandover().details: Request a two-step ownership handover to the caller. The request will automatically expire in 48 hours (172800 seconds) by default.

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the owner to transfer the ownership to `newOwner`.

beforeSwap(address,(address,address,uint.notice: Ensures only the Angstrom singleton can execute swaps.

claimFees(address,address).notice: Sweeps any balance, assumed to be fees, stored in the Angstrom         contract.

invalidateUnorderedNonces(uint256,uint25.notice: Invalidates the bits specified in mask for the bitmap at the word position

lockAcquired(bytes).notice: Executes the UniswapV4 interactions stipulated in the bundle.
